&gt;&gt; And my question is when we
walk in there, it's blaring.

00:09:09.770 --> 00:09:13.836
I love your music selection, and
it's like blaring Jay-Z and--

00:09:14.970 --> 00:09:16.370
&gt;&gt; And We, The Pizza?

00:09:16.970 --> 00:09:17.370
&gt;&gt; And so-- and We, The Pizza, yeah.

00:09:18.970 --> 00:09:19.970
&gt;&gt; Sure.

00:09:20.970 --> 00:09:23.370
&gt;&gt; And then Good Stuff has bought
R and B. What was the inspiration

00:09:22.970 --> 00:09:23.770
or why did you choose
to use that music in?

00:09:24.970 --> 00:09:27.103
&gt;&gt; Well, the probably blazing
Jay-Z 'cause I haven't been there

00:09:26.970 --> 00:09:28.770
for a couple of weeks but--

00:09:28.970 --> 00:09:29.970
[ Laughter ]

00:09:30.970 --> 00:09:31.503
&gt;&gt; Oh, I just told
him that, I'm sorry.

00:09:32.970 --> 00:09:34.236
&gt;&gt; No, I'm kidding.

00:09:34.970 --> 00:09:35.170
I just went to the Jay-Z concert.

00:09:36.970 --> 00:09:37.970
I love him.

00:09:38.970 --> 00:09:40.903
But, you know, the idea of--
well, for those who don't know,

00:09:40.970 --> 00:09:43.036
we just opened-- I recently
opened a new restaurant called We,

00:09:42.970 --> 00:09:44.836
The Pizza about a month ago.

00:09:44.970 --> 00:09:46.570
It's focusing on New York
style pizza, homemade gelato,

00:09:46.970 --> 00:09:49.236
homemade sodas, again encompassing
like really fresh ingredients,

00:09:48.970 --> 00:09:49.903
and we do sell by the
slice which people seem

00:09:50.970 --> 00:09:51.503
to be really excited
about on the Hill.

00:09:52.970 --> 00:09:54.483
But the great question about
the music is that, you know,

00:09:55.190 --> 00:09:55.430
at Good Stuff we actually
started with a rock and roll.

00:09:58.550 --> 00:09:59.186
We play a little bit of reggae
and, yeah, we play some R

00:10:01.580 --> 00:10:02.660
and B sometimes too but I really
think it's important to kind

00:10:04.500 --> 00:10:05.326
of set the ambiance of a
restaurant so when people walk in,

00:10:07.540 --> 00:10:09.540
they're getting an experience.

00:10:09.780 --> 00:10:10.700
&gt;&gt; Sometimes again trouble
for how loud our music is

00:10:12.260 --> 00:10:13.213
if I don't control it, but I just
feel like it just uplifts people

00:10:15.640 --> 00:10:16.183
and makes it interesting and
there's a great environment.

00:10:18.830 --> 00:10:21.630
We chose a different
style of music for We,

00:10:21.930 --> 00:10:26.396
The Pizza because it was my business
partner, Michael Colletti and I

